Human rights and the framework for social rights. Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities. After passing the course, the student will know the bases of lawful practice and be able to define social work from the human rights perspective.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide knowledge of human rights and their implementation in the social field.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows the basic provisions of the framework documents on human rights and social rights, and know how to implement them in order to resolve practical issues; 2) recognizes the fundamental principles set out in the Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities; 3) knows the fundamentals of lawful social work practice; 4) be able to define social work from the perspective of human rights; 5) knows the competence requirements for social workers as well as their assignments regarding the provision and supervision of human rights.
